{"id": 909, "title": "Ticket #909: Resource limit script shouldn't attempt to limit Virtual Memory size", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe default resource limiting script attempts to limit swap space by grabbing the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=VirtualMemory\" title=\"Virtual Memory\">VirtualMemory</a></span> param in a startd ad and using ulimit -v, however that will limit the physical memory + swap space which is not what was intended.  There doesn't seem to currently be a way to use limits to limit swap usage, so remove the restriction all together.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Jul-30 10:30</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/6b146146e10bfdf89bed8331303a11d35338ee23\">[37043]</a></span>: in manual section 3.12.13, condor_limits_wrapper.sh changed in 2010, but developer never documented the change in <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=909\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('909'); return false;\" title=\"Resource limit script shouldn't attempt to limit Virtual Memory size\">#909</a></span>. File copied into the manual is now updated. ===GT=== <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=2433\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('2433'); return false;\" title=\"update examples of tool output throughout manual\">#2433</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2009-Nov-04 12:23</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a